                Mayors Discuss Economic Development and Trade

     Mayor Chavez Addressing the Chihuahua delegation (January 28, 2002)
   Mayor Martin Chavez met on Friday with Mayor Ing. Jorge Barousse Moreno
        of Chihuahua and his delegation. The delegation was visiting
    Albuquerque in an effort to promote a working partnership on economic
   development and international trade. The visit was also a Sister Cities
     Exchange and an opportunity to discuss new technologies, police and
                security, sports, and culture and recreation.

    "It's been an honor to host Mayor Barousse and his delegation," said
     Mayor Chavez. "We ha Chihuahua's Mayor Barousse Talking with Mayor
        Chavez d some provoking discussions regarding water, growth,
    transportation, and other issues common to our region. I see today as
         the beginning of a very cooperative and mutually beneficial
                               relationship."
     The delegation had a full schedule while visiting Albuquerque. The
   agenda included meetings with Sandia National Laboratories, the Mexican
    Consulate, the Mexican Trade Center in Santa Fe, the New Mexico Trade
   Division, the Albuquerque Hispano and Greater Chambers of Commerce, the
   International Trade Council of New Mexico, and the Andersons School of
                                 Management.

